Media notes: agitated adult giving chip calls in alarm along Pine Swamp Trail, probably nesting nearby and almost certainly as a reaction to my presence; titmice join in towards end of audio; 2 audio recordings joined at 0:51 with silenced transition
Observation Details: Abundant breeder here; careful 1x1 counts: 14 along Pine Swamp Trail, 17 while driving Sparta Mt Rd + Weldon Rd, 6 along Ogden Mine Railroad

**High; very careful tally kept throughout walk. Stopped every 2 miles to calculate numbers. Averaging around 10-14 birds per a mile. Many singing with probably more just calling. Many young birds. Majority of birds a long Whitetail loop and Cedar swamp road.

Media notes: Agitated calls from an Ovenbird, hopping from perch to perch on a fallen tree and sometimes onto the ground just off the trail. A second bird was in the vicinity but did not call. Calls apparently given in response to our presence (no playback or pishing).
Adult Ovenbird, sex unknown, giving calls of two types from forest floor. Equipment Notes: Recorder's HPF on (80Hz, -18dB/octave). Elevation: 480 m.

Background Species: Ptiloxena atroviolacea -- Cuban Blackbird; Turdus plumbeus -- Red-legged Thrush; Contopus caribaeus -- Cuban Pewee

Media notes: Adults upset as dog and I passed them. Young in roadside trees and one on ground.
Observation Details: family group of 2 adults plus fledged young, one on ground and others in trees. They were very agitated as we passed. Crowns raised uttering sound below.

Locality: Reserva de la Biosfera Ría Lagartos--Rancho San Salvador
Media notes: Calls in response to pishing. Seen.

Background Species: Cyanocitta cristata -- Blue Jay; Catharus guttatus -- Hermit Thrush; Sitta carolinensis -- White-breasted Nuthatch; Setophaga pinus -- Pine Warbler

Media notes: Agitated calls from a pair carrying food in response to pishing.
Agitated ovenbird that came in along with a HOWA after pishing was used. Clearly seemed territorial, flitting around and flicking its tail.

Locality: Urbana SF—Finger Lakes Trail to Huckleberry Bog
Media notes: Recorded at 0940. The first segment contains one individual, and the second segment contains both members of the pair.
